 for bestpractices and # Admin Dashboard

## Overview
This prompt defines a comprehensive Admin Dashboard feature for ProBid, an operations-centered console that enables admins to review listings, approve buyers, monitor live auctions, perform finance reconciliations, and resolve disputes. It enforces an reusable, RBAC-driven OS workflow, immutable audit logging, and a strict, safety-first development approach. The solution must be built with a reuse-first mindset, integrating with a real-time auction engine, AI/vision checks, and Stripe-based payments, while ensuring runtime safety for all array-like data and API responses as per the project’s mandatory coding standards.

## Page Description (Full Detail)
The Admin Dashboard page is a centralized operations hub enabling admins to:
- Review and process new listings via a structured Ops Review Queue with checklists, attachments, and an auditable trail.
- Approve or deny buyer/KYC requests with documented rationale and audit entries.
- Monitor ongoing and upcoming auctions in real time, with controls to pause, extend, cancel, or intervene as needed.
- Reconcile finances across subscriptions, transactional fees, deposits, payouts, and billing events.
- Manage disputes end-to-end: open disputes list, case notes, evidence uploads, and resolution actions.
- Manage RBAC: assign roles and permissions to internal users, with permission gates on sensitive actions.
- Display key metrics and audit trails (immutable) for regulatory compliance and business needs.

Connected features:
- Ops Review Queue & Workflow: Structured tasks and checklists for approving listings, scheduling inspections, and resolving disputes with an auditable trail.
- Audit & Compliance Logging: Immutable audit logs for critical actions (listing approvals, auction outcomes, payments, dispute resolutions).

UI/UX guidance:
- A high-contrast, modern admin aesthetic with bold action highlights in neon yellow-green for CTAs and data emphasis.
- Clean, left-aligned data presentation with right-aligned numeric indicators where appropriate.
- Real-time data surfaces (auction status, bids, payouts) with minimal latency and clear visual cues for state changes.
- Audit trail entries visible in context panels and searchable/filterable by action type, user, timestamp, and entity.
- Accessibility considerations: keyboard navigable, sufficient color contrast, and ARIA-compliant controls.

API integrations:
- Local app state and Supabase-backed data layer with Edge Functions and Realtime for live updates.
- Optional external services: AI vision checks, enrichment APIs, email/SMS notifications, Stripe webhooks for payments.
- All API interactions must pass through strict input validation and null-safety utilities (see coding standards).

Note: The project context emphasizes a reuse-first approach with strong data integrity, concurrency safety, auditability, and modularity. The Admin Dashboard should be built to scale with future integrations (AI checks, external verifications, and additional RBAC scopes).

## Components to Build
- Ops Review Queue Component
  - Tasks: approve, reject, request changes; structured checklist; audit trail entry per action.
  - Attachments: support for listing evidence, inspection reports, and messages.
  - State: per-listing task progress, due dates, and inspector assignment.
  - Data: listing details, approvals, changes history (immutable audit events).
  - UI: card-based queue with filters, search, and status chips; inline action buttons.
- Buyer Approvals Console
  - KYC status list, document list with upload/view, approval/denial actions.
  - Audit trail linkage to approvals and user notes.
- Auction Monitor
  - Live auctions list with bid activity, pause/cancel/extend controls, and risk alerts.
  - Real-time updates via Supabase Realtime/WebSockets; optimistic UI with reconciliation.
- Finance Panel
  - Subscriptions revenue, transactional fees, deposits ledger, payout scheduling.
  - Interactive charts and tabular ledgers; export options.
- Dispute Management Center
  - Open disputes list with case notes, evidence uploads, chat/logs, escalation path.
  - Resolution actions (resolve, escalate, request additional info) with audit entries.
- RBAC Management
  - Roles, permissions, user assignments; per-action gating with audit logging.
  - RBAC editor with validation (no conflicting permissions, inheritance handling).
- Audit Log Viewer
  - Immutable, searchable, filterable audit logs across modules; exportable reports.
- Global Admin Utilities
  - User search, system health checks, activity dashboards, notifications center.
- UI Shell
  - Persistent bottom navigation (non-collapsible), top header with user info and global controls.
  - Shared components: Card, Button, Input, Select, DatePicker, Checkbox, Tabs, Badge, Avatar.

Technical notes:
- All data surfaces must guard against null or undefined values before invoking array methods (.map, .filter, .reduce, etc.) per the runtime safety rules.
- Supabase results should use data ?? [] and type guards (Array.isArray) where appropriate.
- Initialize React state for arrays with useState<Type[]>([]) and avoid useState() for arrays/objects.
- Validate API response shapes before consuming (const list = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : []).

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- Framework: Next.js 14+ with App Router, TypeScript.
- Styling: Tailwind CSS with design tokens aligned to the provided color palette.
- UI Components:
  - Reusable Card, Button (filled and outlined), Input, TextArea, Select, DatePicker, Switch, Tabs, Tag, Avatar, Icon set (outline geometric icons).
  - Data visualization: minimalist horizontal bar charts with neon yellow-green fill for active segments.
- Pages/Routes:
  - /admin/dashboard (Admin Dashboard main hub)
  - /admin/dashboard/ops (Ops Review Queue)
  - /admin/dashboard/buyers (Buyer Approvals)
  - /admin/dashboard/auctions (Auction Monitor)
  - /admin/dashboard/finance (Finance)
  - /admin/dashboard/disputes (Dispute Management)
  - /admin/dashboard/rbac (RBAC)
  - /admin/dashboard/audit-logs (Audit Logs)
- Real-time data:
  - Subscriptions to Supabase Realtime channels for auctions, listings, disputes, and payments.
  - Ensure proper handling if real-time data is temporarily unavailable.
- Accessibility:
  - Keyboard focus outlines, ARIA attributes, and semantic HTML where applicable.
- Security/RBAC:
  - UI-level gating based on user roles; visible controls should be disabled or hidden if not authorized.
- Form Validation:
  - Sanitize and validate inputs (e.g., IDs, document uploads, dates, monetary amounts).
- Data Safeguards:
  - All array data must be guarded: (items ?? []).map(...) and Array.isArray(items) ? items.map(...) : [].
- Testing:
  - Component-level unit tests for array-safe handlers and edge cases.
  - E2E tests simulating login, RBAC gating, queue operations, and audit log creation.

### Backend
- Database: Supabase Postgres with RLS enabled.
- Tables (core models):
  - listings(id, seller_id, status, created_at, updated_at, audit_log_id)
  - buyers(id, status, kyc_documents, created_at, updated_at)
  - auctions(id, listing_id, status, current_bid, reserve_price, end_time, paused, extended, audit_log_id)
  - bids(id, auction_id, bidder_id, amount, timestamp)
  - deposits(id, buyer_id, amount, currency, timestamp)
  - subscriptions(id, buyer_id, plan_id, status, started_at, ends_at)
  - payments(id, payer_id, amount, currency, status, timestamp, stripe_invoice_id)
  - disputes(id, related_entity_type, related_entity_id, status, case_notes, evidence_links, created_at)
  - audit_logs(id, action, entity_type, entity_id, user_id, metadata, created_at, immutable)
  - roles(id, name, permissions jsonb, created_at)
  - users_roles(user_id, role_id)
  - permissions (optional helper)
- Functions/Endpoints:
  - Admin OS actions:
    - approveListing(listing_id, reason)
    - rejectListing(listing_id, reason)
    - requestListingChanges(listing_id, checklist)
    - approveBuyer(buyer_id, decision, notes)
    - pauseAuction(auction_id), extendAuction(auction_id, extension)
    - resolveDispute(dispute_id, resolution, notes)
    - assignRole(user_id, role_id)
  - Finance:
    - reconcileSubscriptions()
    - recordPaymentEvent(event_type, payload)
  - Auditing:
    - logAudit(action, entity_type, entity_id, user_id, metadata)
  - RBAC:
    - getUserPermissions(user_id), assignPermissions(user_id, permissions)
- Data safety:
  - All query results guarded with data ?? [] and Array.isArray checks.
  - Use edge functions for sensitive mutations; idempotent webhooks for Stripe.
- Validation:
  - Input schemas with runtime validation and default fallbacks.
- API routing:
  - Use REST-ish or RPC-like endpoints under /api/admin/... with proper authentication.

### Integration
- Data Flow:
  - Admin UI actions call backend endpoints; backend writes audit_logs immutably; frontend subscribes to real-time channels for updates.
  - Audit logs feed the Audit Log viewer and export functions.
- Real-time:
  - Supabase Realtime channels for auctions, listings, disputes, and payments.
  - UI should gracefully degrade if realtime is down, with a manual refresh option.
- External Services:
  - AI Vision checks integrated as a pluggable service interface; provide fallbacks to rules-based validation if vision API is unavailable.
  - Email/SMS notifications facade for approvals, disputes, and payout events.
  - Stripe webhooks for payments and subscriptions; ensure idempotency tokens are honored.

## User Experience Flow
- Admin Landing:
  - Scan quick metrics (open disputes, pending approvals, auctions live, total revenue) using a dashboard overview.
- Ops Review Queue:
  - Filter by status, risk, seller, or deadline; click a listing to open a detail panel with checklist items; perform approve/reject/request changes; attach evidence; automatic audit-log entry creation.
- Buyer Approvals:
  - View KYC status; review documents; approve/deny with notes; trigger audit log; optional auto-notifications.
- Auction Monitor:
  - See live auctions; hover to view bidding heat; pause/extend/cancel; see bid history and auction events; audit trail for interventions.
- Finance Panel:
  - View revenue streams by period; reconcile deposits vs payouts; schedule payouts; export ledgers; view audit entries for financial events.
- Disputes:
  - Open disputes list; inspect case notes and uploaded evidence; add internal notes; apply resolution actions; audit log.
- RBAC:
  - Create roles, assign permissions to users; enforce in UI and via backend checks; audit changes.

## Technical Specifications

- Data Models: (Excerpts)
  - audit_logs: id, action, entity_type, entity_id, user_id, metadata jsonb, created_at, immutable boolean
  - listings: id, seller_id, status, created_at, updated_at, audit_log_id
  - auctions: id, listing_id, status, current_bid, reserve_price, end_time, paused, extended, audit_log_id
  - disputes: id, related_entity_type, related_entity_id, status, case_notes text, evidence_links text[], created_at
  - payments: id, payer_id, amount numeric, currency text, status text, timestamp, stripe_invoice_id
  - users_roles: user_id, role_id
  - roles: id, name, permissions jsonb
- API Endpoints (Examples):
  - POST /api/admin/listings/:id/approve
  - POST /api/admin/listings/:id/reject
  - POST /api/admin/listings/:id/request-changes
  - POST /api/admin/buyers/:id/approve
  - POST /api/admin/auctions/:id/pause
